* **O(1) `get` / `set`** – constant‑time lookup and updates.  
* **LRU eviction** – when the cache would grow beyond `maxSize` we must discard the *least‑recently‑used* entry.  
* **TTL per entry** – a value lives only for a limited time.  We do **lazy expiry**: the entry is removed only when we try to read it (or when it is evicted because of LRU pressure).  

The classic solution for an *LRU* cache is a **hash table + doubly‑linked list**.  
The *hash table* gives O(1) key → node mapping.  
The *list* keeps the usage order: the **head** is the most‑recently‑used, the **tail** the least‑recently‑used.  

The **key trick** for adding TTL while keeping O(1) operations is **to store the *absolute* expiry timestamp on the node itself** (`expiresAt = Date.now() + ttl`).  
When a key is accessed we simply compare `Date.now()` with that timestamp.  
No extra timer, priority‑queue, or periodic sweep is needed – the expiry check is *lazy* and costs O(1) exactly where we already have O(1) work.

---

## Implementation (plain JavaScript)

```js
// ---------------------------------------------------------------
//  LRU cache with per‑entry TTL (lazy expiry)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------
class LruTtl {
  /**
   * @param {number} maxSize      – maximum number of entries.
   * @param {number} defaultTtlMs – TTL (ms) used when set() is called without ttl.
   */
  constructor(maxSize, defaultTtlMs) {
    if (maxSize <= 0) throw new Error('maxSize must be > 0');
    this.maxSize = maxSize;
    this.defaultTtlMs = defaultTtlMs ?? Infinity; // Infinity means “never expires”

    // key → node
    this.map = new Map();

    // Doubly‑linked list (sentinel nodes for easier edge handling)
    this.head = { prev: null, next: null }; // most‑recent
    this.tail = { prev: null, next: null }; // least‑recent
    this.head.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = this.head;

    this.size = 0;
  }

  // -----------------------------------------------------------------
  // Public API
  // -----------------------------------------------------------------
  /** Returns the stored value or undefined if missing / expired */
  get(key) {
    const node = this.map.get(key);
    if (!node) return undefined;                // not in cache

    // ---- lazy expiry test ----
    if (node.expiresAt <= Date.now()) {
      this._removeNode(node);
      this.map.delete(key);
      this.size--;
      return undefined;                         // expired
    }

    // move to head because it is now most‑recently‑used
    this._moveToHead(node);
    return node.value;
  }

  /**
   * Store a value.
   * @param {*} key
   * @param {*} value
   * @param {number} [ttlMs] – overrides the default TTL for this entry.
   */
  set(key, value, ttlMs) {
    const now = Date.now();
    const ttl = ttlMs !== undefined ? ttlMs : this.defaultTtlMs;
    const expiresAt = now + ttl;

    let node = this.map.get(key);
    if (node) {
      // update existing entry
      node.value = value;
      node.expiresAt = expiresAt;
      this._moveToHead(node);
      return;
    }

    // ----- create a brand‑new node -----
    node = {
      key,
      value,
      expiresAt,
      prev: null,
      next: null,
    };
    this.map.set(key, node);
    this._addToHead(node);
    this.size++;

    // ----- LRU eviction if we overflow -----
    if (this.size > this.maxSize) {
      const lru = this.tail.prev; // real tail node (never the sentinel)
      this._removeNode(lru);
      this.map.delete(lru.key);
      this.size--;
    }
  }

  /** For debugging / tests – returns true if a key is present (even if expired) */
  _has(key) {
    return this.map.has(key);
  }

  // -----------------------------------------------------------------
  // Internal helpers – all O(1)
  // -----------------------------------------------------------------
  _addToHead(node) {
    // Insert right after the sentinel head
    node.prev = this.head;
    node.next = this.head.next;
    this.head.next.prev = node;
    this.head.next = node;
  }

  _removeNode(node) {
    node.prev.next = node.next;
    node.next.prev = node.prev;
    // break links to aid GC
    node.prev = node.next = null;
  }

  _moveToHead(node) {
    this._removeNode(node);
    this._addToHead(node);
  }
}

